stylometry: Optimization is using all your resources in order to maximize profits while incuring minimal costs. Components of linear programing are. Objective function, it is our main goal of a given problem, or  what we are trying to solve for in a given scenario, whether it be to maximize profits or to minimize costs, these are both examples of an objective function. It is also the target cell in the excel sheet. Decision variables are the information variables, that is they give us information about particular variables in a problem that will force us to choose between variables. Decision variables are using the changing cells in an excel program.Constraints are restraints put on variables within a problem. These restraints will limit our resources in a given problem. Then there is feasible region which is the possible area on a graph to which the optimal solution can be found. Corner points are end points within a feasible region that gives a better idea where the optimal solution can be found.
